You know, Iâ€™ve grown quite fond of this ring I have. I think I wouldnâ€™t mind wearing two of them! I think I would actually quite prefer it. Iâ€™d even like to get you one.. If you would like? Why am I afraid of Halloween? When I first left Chateau Rateau, my ancestral home, I thought October 31st was a regular beautiful day. But when I reached the local town, couldnâ€™t believe how scary the outside world was! The cobwebs? Gravestones? Skeletons everywhere?! Iâ€™d never left the grounds before, and almost started to cry. The Hot Wheels I saw was bright green and vibrant. It reminded me of my familyâ€™s lost emeralds. This is my first time in a city, and everything is so new! Year 5, I get married. Year 6, you â€” I mean, whoever my future partner isâ€” and I have 3 baby rats and then we have a perfect family of 5 clowns.

Iâ€™m a critically acclaimed ice-cream toppings coordinator. I studied abroad on full scholarship in my ratdolesence. I studied amongst the finest in my field and truly got in touch with my personal, professional, and artistic motivations

When I was abroad, my ice cream artistry class had a large focus on a strong conceptual backing, rather than just focusing on creating a technically perfect cone. With this, the nuance of choice entered my mind, a focus on the why not the how.

I graduated, top of my class, with honors of the highest caliber. More important to me than my academic standing was my self fulfilment in certifiably having mastered my craft. However, my pursuit is lifelong and I know I will continue to learn and perfect past mastery.

Hi! I'm Muffy. Though my looks are enthralling and ginormous, I am really just a regular ant! I used to be petit and microscopic but I've been consuming some miracle-gro on a regular basis, and, well, I grew!

My favorite food used to be fish flakes and nerds clusters, but now that my taste-buds have developed and I find them rather.. frivolous. My taste-buds formed around the same time that my vocal chords did - it's true! Had you seen me but a week ago we would be unable to partake in the joys of conversation.

Actually my closest friend and confidant,  Manndy - who is a rat much like yourself, believed me to be a youth before I was able to talk, and was shocked to find that we are the same age! While sharing a meal - my favorite, Miracle-gro: (drought-tolerant) garden soil roses - we where comparing our star charts and found out that they are exactly the same! Functionally, we are twins, Manndy and I, but we have lived such different lives.

I was an architect back in my old anthill, the famous West Montana East-Village Unit E Anthill. It was quite the stressful lifestyle, digging and digging, building and building. But it is also easy as we are so strong. I'm considering writing a book about my time spent with single-segment thorax-free mannals like rats, as I think the ants at home will be fascinated. What is it like not being able to lift 5000 times your weight? You make it look effortless and chic

Just this last week I had the honor of winning the award for biggest ant. It was a blast. Maybe in my top 10 events I have experienced in my many years alive. I won at the Best Ants Annual Award Show. The other competitions at the show where extremely exciting. Next year I'm keen to see who wins Most Aerodynamic, Most Polished Thorax, Hunkiest Ant... dreamiest eyes (I think actually you may have the dreamiest eyes now that I'm looking).
